{
  "name": "2003-06-sarbanes-oxley-insight-pt2-veytsel-3950f2",
  "title": "Melding Financial Operations and Analytics: The New Financial Battleground",
  "description": "Alex Veytsel of Aberdeen Group argues that the Sarbanes-Oxley Act is accelerating convergence between Financial Value Chain Management (FVCM) and financial analytics software, creating a corporate performance management imperative. The insight categorizes three supplier heritage types\u2014financial analytics vendors, FVCM specialists, and ERP companies\u2014evaluating each against SOX compliance needs, with ERP vendors holding a trump card via general ledger control. Aberdeen predicts that innovative FVCM suppliers will either add analytic capability or be displaced, and that SOX-driven transparency will prove beneficial beyond compliance.",
